body:
hello guys,


i was verilating some designs and i have an expected ( i think results).


For instance, i was trying to verilate a file (file_1.v) that cointains modules declarations (verilated with the hierachical approaches) 
File_1.v : 
```
/* verilator lint_off DECLFILENAME */
/* verilator lint_off MULTITOP */
module my_and(A1, A2, Z);
 /*verilator hier_block*/
  input A1;
  input A2;
  output Z;

  and(Z, A1, A2);
endmodule

module my_and2(A1, A2, Z);
 /*verilator hier_block*/
  input A1;
  input A2;
  output Z;

  and(Z, A1, A2);
endmodule
```
the above modules are instantiated into another file.

The point is that for each module in file_1.v i was creating the static libraries,  and then link the libraries when verilating file_2.v

However, the static libraries have been created except for module my_end.

The workaround, i found is the following:
```
`module fake(a);
input a;
endmodule 


module my_and(A1, A2, Z);
 /*verilator hier_block*/
  input A1;
  input A2;
  output Z;

  and(Z, A1, A2);
endmodule

module my_and2(A1, A2, Z);
 /*verilator hier_block*/
  input A1;
  input A2;
  output Z;

  and(Z, A1, A2);
endmodule
```

am i missing something? is it related to top module, i.e., verilator expects a top module inside each verilog file?

Verilator version 5.018
OS ubuntu 20.04

Thanks!
